narratives.question_text:
What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
(Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: I learned how to play various gamelan instruments and understood some of the cultural philosophies behind the gamelan tradition.
I learned about gamelan music which is super awesome and easy to get into. You learn how to play different instruments and you also learn a fair amount about the context of gamelan music in Java.

narratives.question_text:
What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
(Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: I very much enjoyed the rehearsal structure of the course, but I would have liked to hear a little more on the background of each piece.

Playing together as an ensemble is a great part of this course, but I wish there was more reading in the course. I read a gamelan music book for another class while taking this course and felt that my knowledge and even playing improved greatly because of it.

narratives.question_text: Among the practices in this course geared toward learning during the COVID-19 pandemic, which succeeded and which could be improved? Please comment on course practices that allowed for virtual engagement. (Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: Nice to have a limited in-person class during this semester!

narratives.question_text:
Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
(Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: Yes. I felt like it was a good way to engage with non-Western traditional music and had a great time learning to play the various instruments.

yes, take this course. Masdar and Maho are both great and you'll enjoy taking a break from other types of classes at Yale while playing in the ensemble. gamelan music is also a rich source of inspiration if you're willing to put the time into it.
Yes, nice intro to ethnomusicology and the practice of gamelan!
Absolutely! If anyone has a free class ever during their time at Yale, I would recommend this course for a wonderful experience.

comments: Part of the course was virtual during the campus quarantine, but then we got to play in the ensemble together.
